      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAHLUA GIRL (2) is a former Qld'er safely held fresh for the stable then ran a good race at the provincials last time. This easier and has placed 2/2 when third-up from a break. Looks well placed and with good speed will give a sight. Joining her up front will be ZATANNA (1) who has been going very well this circuit with a couple of runs in town in between. Has good speed and will tale catching off the inside. SAMANTH (4) scored a big win here last time and drawn for a good trail. UNCLE BARRY (3) will find this easier. Placed 2/2 this circuit and expect he will make amends. SCANDALIST (5) is capable open best figures and gets chance to atone.",
